<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="135" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="36.[212,1444,1167,1434]" pageId="36" pageNumber="135">
DESCRIPTION. — By and large agreeing with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1916" box="[705,842,1168,1192]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Anomalodermus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ignambius">
<emphasis box="[705,842,1168,1192]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="135">H. ignambius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except for having the abbreviated striae 4 and 5 ending on the elytral dorsum, thus lacking a small, low, densely squamose knob or tubercle on the space between striae 3 and 6 at the upper part of the declivity just below the tubercle of interstria 3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[212,1444,1167,1434]" pageId="36" pageNumber="135">Male: aedeagus more strongly converging apicad, before apex only one-half of the width at base; basal sclerite similar but shorter, as long as aedeagal body.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[212,1444,1167,1434]" pageId="36" pageNumber="135">Female: tergite 8 at base pale, not intensely pigmented; spermathecal duct extension short, considerably shorter than the spermathecal hook; spermathecal duct 2.5 x as long as spermatheca.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[212,1444,1167,1434]" box="[242,472,1410,1434]" pageId="36" pageNumber="135">
Length: 
<quantity box="[330,468,1410,1434]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.25" metricValueMin="0.75" pageId="36" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="10.0" valueMax="12.5" valueMin="7.5">7.5-12.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
